msgid "Spot Volumetric Effects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:10
msgid "Spot lamps' Halo options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:12
msgid ""
"*Spot* lights also can produce \"volumetric\" effects. See :doc:`Volumetric "
"Light </render/blender_render/lighting/volumetric_lights>` for more information "
"about what it means."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:20
msgid "Halo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:17
msgid ""
"The *Halo* button allows a *Spot* lamp to have a volumetric effect applied to "
"it. This button must be active if the volumetric effect is to be visible. Note "
"that if you are using buffered shadows, you will have extra options described "
"in the :doc:`Spot Buffered Shadows </render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/"
"buffered_shadow>` page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:25
msgid "Intensity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:23
msgid ""
"The *Intensity* slider controls how intense/dense the volumetric effect is that "
"is generated from the light source. The lower the value of the *Intensity* "
"slider, the less visible the volumetric effect is, while higher *Intensity* "
"values give a much more noticeable and dense volumetric effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:33
msgid "Step"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:28
msgid ""
"This field can have a value between (0 to 12). It is used to determine whether "
"this *Spot* will cast volumetric shadows, and what quality those volumetric "
"shadows will have. If *Step* is set to a value of 0, then no volumetric shadow "
"will be generated. Unlike most other controls, as the *Step* value increases, "
"the quality of volumetric shadows decreases (but take less time to render), and "
"*vice versa*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:35
msgid "Step values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:37
msgid ""
"A value of 8 for *Halo Step* is usually a good compromise between speed and "
"accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:39
msgid ""
"Blender only simulates volumetric lighting in *Spot* lamps when using its "
"internal renderer. This can lead to some strange results for certain "
"combinations of settings for the light's *Energy* and the halo's *Intensity*. "
"For example, having a *Spot* light with null or very low light *Energy* "
"settings but a very high halo *Intensity* setting can result in a dark/black "
"halo, which would not happen in the real world. Just be aware of this "
"possibility when using halos with the internal renderer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/halo.rst:48
msgid ""
"The halo effect can be greatly enhanced when using buffered shadows: when the "
"halo's *Step* is not null, they can create \"volumetric shadows\". See the page "
"about *Spot* :doc:`Buffered Shadows </render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/"
"buffered_shadow>` for more information."
msgstr ""

